column5: It took 57.4 lbs to win and i think over 50lbs to place, from what i am hearing it was a pretty good bite with lots of big fish being caught. As with all tournaments on the river it is usually the good under 55cm fish that are the hardest to catch and are key to the win.

Top 25 was 42 lbs. It was a tougher bite then usual with lots of small fish, little cigars. I agree the slots are important but without the overs your done. You can stay in it with 3 ok slots and two good overs. The big fish were hard to find all week compared to other years.
